commText: We're back for the chase.. Kwena Maphaka to start for MI, two slips in place

MI innings progression Overs 1-4: 20/4 (RR: 5.00) Overs 5-7: 39/0 (RR: 13.00) Overs 8-10: 18/1 (RR: 6.00) Overs 11-15: 25/2 (RR: 5.00) Overs 16-20: 23/2 (RR: 4.60) Pace vs spin in RR innings Spin: 3/38 in 8 overs (ER 4.75) Pace: 6/84 in 12 overs (ER 7.00) Most 3-wicket hauls in the IPL 20 - Jasprit Bumrah 20 - Yuzvendra Chahal* 19 - Lasith Malinga 17 - Amit MIshra Lowest 1st innings totals for MI vs RR 94/8 at Jaipur, 2011 125/9 at Wankhede, 2024* 133/5 at Wankhede, 2011 145/7 at Jaipur, 2008 - 125/9 by MI is also the lowest total in this year's IPL

Chahal: Was trying to vary my pace, just tried to mix my length and pace. A few balls were turning, so I tried to bowl that ball against Hardik. I always back my skills, this is the format where you go for runs, sometimes you get wickets. There's little dew, but we need to play well in the first six overs.

21:20 Local Time, 15:50 GMT, 21:20 IST: A disappointing batting effort, but credit to the 'BBC' trio of the Royals who kept it very tight and were relentless - Boult struck twice in the 1st over, followed it up with another in the 3rd and Burger had MI reeling at 20 for 4 in the 4th when he dismissed Ishan Kishan. A brief recovery followed as Hardik Pandya and Tilak Varma counter-punched, but Chahal came into his own, dismissing both as MI once again slipped from 76 for 4 to 114 for 9. That 56-run run 5th wicket stand was the lone saving grace for the hosts who looked lost. The new ball swung and their batters looked helpless. 126 should be a cakewalk for the Royals, especially against an attack that conceded 277 in the last match, but MI will believe they can fight back if they strike early. The chase coming up shortly..

Avesh Khan to Akash Madhwal, 2 runs, fuller length delivery on off, driven to the left of mid-off where Buttler dives to prevent a certian boundary - they're coming back for the second, the throw is very wide and Madhwal almost runs into Samson, he can't collect it cleanly and MI finish with 125

Avesh Khan to Bumrah, 1 run, back of a length and angling into Bumrah's body - he's tangled up on the pull, gets a top-edge that drops well in front of long-on

Avesh Khan to Bumrah, FOUR, cracking shot, handy runs for MI - banged in short by Avesh, but it doesn't bounce a lot and is swatted over mid-wicket, wide of the fielder in the deep for a one-bounce boundary

Nandre Burger to Bumrah, no run, the slower bouncer, Bumrah is early into the crouched swing and missed - bounced in front of Samson who doesn't collect it cleanly, but they decide against a bye

Banged in short and he took it on with the pull, didn't bother to keep it down - Boult ran across to his right, reverse cup, and held on with ease. Tim David c Boult b Nandre Burger 17(24) [4s-1]

Nandre Burger [3.0-0-31-1] is back into the attack
Royals have activated their impact substitute - Shubham Dubey replaces Yuzvendra Chahal. Burger, from round the wicket

Avesh Khan to Tim David, no run, on a good length and around the off-stump channel, pushed straight to the fielder at cover
Avesh Khan to Tim David, no run, banged in short and at the stumps, David drops his wrists and sways away from the line

Catching practice at cover - a deliciously bowled floater, right up in Coetzee's eyeline - the right-hander couldn't resist at playing the drive, but he does so without any conviction. A mere chip and it's a dolly for Hetmyer at cover. MI continue to lose their way. Coetzee c Hetmyer b Chahal 4(9)

Boult to Gerald Coetzee, 1 run, fuller length delivery and well wide of off, driven in front of square on the off-side for a single
Boult to Tim David, 1 run, fuller length delivery and well wide of off, driven in front of square on the off-side for a single

They've taken the strategic break with MI finding themselves in a desperate situation. At best, they can try and bat out their 20 overs, hopefully getting around 140, but will it be enough against an in-form batting unit?

Chahal to Tilak Varma, out Caught by Ashwin!! Oh dear! This is going from bad to worse for the Mumbai Indians - Was thrown up full and wide of off, could've been a wide had Tilak let it go, but he's committed into playing it - he has to reach out to such an extent that he loses his balance on the cut, gets a thick top-edge that lobbed to the left of Ashwin at short third man, he moves across, dives and holds on. MI are in a hole now - can they even bat out the 20 overs? Tilak Varma c Ashwin b Chahal 32(29) [6s-2]

Avesh Khan to Chawla, out Caught by Hetmyer!! Mumbai Indians sink further! And how about that catch by Hetmyer! Was a short of a length delivery outside off and Chawla carved it towards backward point. Hetmyer dives to his right and completes a terrific catch. The ploy to send Chawla up the order hasn't worked for the hosts. Chawla c Hetmyer b Avesh Khan 3(6)

Strategic timeout! Quite an eventful start to this match. Boult took three early wickets in the form of Rohit, Naman and Brevis, while Kishan was dismissed by Burger within the powerplay itself. Since then, Tilak and Hardik have steadied the ship somewhat, but MI would want this pair to carry on..

Nandre Burger to Ishan Kishan, out Caught by Samson!! Would you believe it? Mumbai Indians are four down! None of their batters are willing to fight it out. Nothing to take away from the RR bowlers either, they are on a roll. This was short and quick outside off, nice bounce and carry, Ishan Kishan has a poke at it and gets a thick outside edge that has been taken by Samson! Mumbai in desperate need for someone to brave them out. Ishan Kishan c Samson b Nandre Burger 16(14) [4s-2 6s-1]
